#chapter_two
@chapter |number II| |title The Voice|

Attention, as @weil argued, is the rarest form of generosity.

The hatch opens anyway. A stranger hauls themselves up, soaked
through, cradling a tin. Berger @berger would have called this
*looking* — but Aldous, in the moment, only knew it as arrival.

